A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 9 of Chapter 12 of Title 16 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to access to medical cannabis, so as to repeal certain advertising restrictions on
3 licensees; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
5 SECTION 1.
6 Article 9 of Chapter 12 of Title 16 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
7 access to medical cannabis, is amended by revising Code Section 16-12-215, relating to
8 limitation on locations, advertising or marketing prohibited, and information available to
9 physicians, as follows:
10 "16-12-215.
11 (a) No licensee shall operate in any location, whether for cultivation, harvesting, and
12 processing of marijuana or for processing, manufacturing, packaging, or distributing low
13 THC oil or products, within a 3,000 foot radius of a covered entity, measured from
14 property boundary to property boundary. No dispensing licensee may operate in any
15 location within a 1,000 foot radius of a covered entity, measured from property boundary
16 to property boundary. Notwithstanding the provisions of this subsection, local
